                            <comment id="17638602" author="gyfora" created="Fri, 25 Nov 2022 09:36:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=fanrui&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;fanrui&quot;&gt;fanrui&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for jumping on this and testing it.&lt;br/&gt;
Probably the minicluster is started with fix resources and that is not enough after scaling up. You could try to allocate more tas slots in the minicluster than the job initially needs so you can scale up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17638616" author="fanrui" created="Fri, 25 Nov 2022 10:22:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gyfora&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gyfora&quot;&gt;gyfora&lt;/a&gt; , thanks for your quick feedback.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I run a flink job in IDEA, I didn&apos;t set any conf for the minicluster. Flink helps user start the minicluster by&#160;maximumParallelism of all tasks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is my demo: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/1996fanrui/flink/commit/52692249c86cbc366f3e5fb54d7744da75586972&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/1996fanrui/flink/commit/52692249c86cbc366f3e5fb54d7744da75586972&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And I have updated the PR, it can fix this bug. In other words: minicluster should adapt &lt;em&gt;jobvertex-parallelism-overrides&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And I will add some tests later.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

